subjectline.content: A More Reliable Polyethylene Supply Chain

preheader.content: Shell Polymers’ PE plant is here to make your life easier.

html.content:
%%[IF _messagecontext == "SEND" AND jobid > 0 THEN set @VAWPLink = view_email_url set @subscriberkey = _subscriberkey ENDIF]%% %%[IF _messagecontext != "VAWP" THEN]%% %%[ENDIF]%%
To view this email as a web page, click here.
Because of our state-of-the-art systems, processes, and culture, our team can focus more on providing a more reliable polyethylene supply.
Our on-site technology is the best of the best and converters can count on our state-of-the-art machinery to run properly and efficiently. Supported by Polymer Pioneers and Pros with over 750 collective years of experience, we offer converters a relationship built to last.
Ranging from conversion knowledge to analytics and quality control, we have a diverse array of capabilities in our new Innovation Center that ensures you can have confidence in our supply and focus on growing your business.
Explore the Plant
We are dedicated to our customer’s success and this means we take the time to understand each customer’s unique business needs. We brought in the most knowledgeable experts so that customers are assured that they are receiving the best guidance.

No matter what area of processing our customers are dealing with, we have the means to ensure that each process goes off seamlessly.

preheader.content: And we’re bringing a more reliable PE supply to your backyard.

html.content:
To view this email as a web page, click here.
That’s why we’ve brought in leadership and technical experts with 750+ years of collective PE experience. No matter which applications you specialize in, our team shares technical tips and industry updates that will help you achieve your business goals.
As we invest in this new facility, we are committed to lead the plastics sector toward social responsibility. That’s why we helped found the Alliance to End Plastic Waste, a nonprofit that’s committed $1.5 billion to reduce plastic waste in the environment.

For example, Shell announced it has successfully made high-end chemicals using a liquid feedstock made from plastic waste. The technique, known as pyrolysis, is considered a breakthrough for hard-to-recycle plastics.
